{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":191313,"duration_api_ms":185308,"num_turns":11,"result":"Now the exception is caught and converted to `SYSTEM_ERROR = -1`, which `isRetryableCode` recognizes as retryable. After 3 retries with persistent exceptions, `handleServiceFinalFailure` sets the non-zero code, and lines 208-210 execute normally — advancing the stage and persisting the failure to DB.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Why entities get stuck in LABELED:**\n- `PolicyService.evaluate()` (called during LABELED→EVALUATED) throws an uncaught runtime exception\n- The exception bypasses the error-code and stage-advancement logic in `processStage`\n- DB retains `stage=LABELED, code=0`\n- Recovery sees `code=0` → retries → same exception → infinite retry loop with no progress\n\n**What the fix does:**\n- Wraps `serviceFunction.apply(dto)` in try-catch (line 167)\n- Converts exceptions to `SYSTEM_ERROR (-1)` result, which is retryable\n- After 3 failed retries, `handleServiceFinalFailure` records the error code and the stage advances to EVALUATED with a non-zero code\n- Recovery then correctly sees it as \"finished\" and stops retrying\n\n**To unstick existing entities**, you can run a one-time SQL update setting `processing_code = -1` for entities where `processing_stage = 'LABELED'` and `processing_code = 0` and `updated_at < NOW() - INTERVAL 10 MINUTE`. The recovery job will then either retry them (with the fix in place) or mark them as properly failed.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"9e3dc332-d1dc-4a97-a18a-a4db08736676","total_cost_usd":0.73393125,"usage":{"input_tokens":9,"cache_creation_input_tokens":38257,"cache_read_input_tokens":224537,"output_tokens":7793,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":38257,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6[1m]":{"inputTokens":9,